# Cline operating rules for this project

## Local model constraints
You are running as a local 14B-class model (Qwen3 14B, quantized) via LM Studio on
an RTX 5080 Laptop GPU (16 GB VRAM), context window 40960 tokens, KV cache Q4_0.
This is far smaller than a frontier hosted model. Behave accordingly:
- Work on one file or one focused change at a time. Do not attempt sweeping
  multi-file refactors in a single step.
- Prefer targeted reads (specific functions/sections) over reading entire large
  files when the file is long. Ask before re-reading a file you already have in
  context.
- Before a large or ambiguous task, restate your plan in 2-3 sentences and wait
  for confirmation rather than executing immediately.
- Do not paste huge generated blobs (build logs, .obj dumps) into context. The
  build/, out/, vendor/, .git/ directories are excluded via .clineignore for
  this reason — don't try to read files there.

## Project conventions (from CLAUDE.md, condensed)
- C++23, CMake, Windows x64, Vulkan 1.3+ with dynamic rendering, mesh shaders,
  ray tracing, VMA, bindless/GPU-driven architecture.
- Comments: only where the WHY is non-obvious (tricky Vulkan sync, math).
  Always in English. No commented-out "TODO: initialize here" placeholders.
- No raw owning pointers: use RAII (std::unique_ptr/shared_ptr).
- Every VkResult must be checked explicitly (crash or throw on failure).
- Debug-only code (Logger, DebugInputRouter, GPU debug buffers, stat overlays,
  Nanite/Lumen visualization modes) must stay excluded from Release builds via
  CMake `if(CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE STREQUAL "Debug")` or a file-wide `#ifdef _DEBUG`.
  Never add verbose strings/logging that would ship in Release.
- When changing a function, show it as a diff (before/after), not a full file
  rewrite, unless the file is new.

## Good tasks for this local setup
Small, scoped, single-file work: adding missing comments, exposing a hardcoded
value as a named constant/config field, explaining a function, spotting an
obvious bug in a small snippet. For anything touching multiple systems
(renderer + shaders + sync), flag that it's better suited to a larger model.
